Kirimari MCA Collo Muchiri has complained over Embu townâ€™s neglect. He said on Thursday most streets are untarmacked and garbage is uncollected. Muchiri said the town, which is part of his Kirimari ward, has been neglected by the county administratio. He said the town, which which should be the face of the county, is an eyesore. It is dirty and needs a facelift in a bid to attract investors, he said. The MCA said he would work with the county government to ensure all the streets in the town are tamarcked starting with Kiambuthi road. He spoke when he flagged off a new ambulance, which he has bought with funds from donors and his own contribution. It will be used for ferryingcritical patients to hospitals free of charge. He warned his opponents said criticism for the sake of it.